TensorFlow is an open-source software library for machine learning and artificial intelligence developed by Google Brain Team. It provides a comprehensive ecosystem of tools and libraries for building and training machine learning models, including neural networks, deep learning, reinforcement learning, and distributed computing. TensorFlow supports multiple programming languages such as Python, C++, and Java, and can run on various platforms like CPUs, GPUs, and TPUs (Tensor Processing Units).
